CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 8, 1941, pg. 9 reads: "Debs All Set For Sweethearts' Ball With Lunceford Ork - Here are pictured some of the Debs About Town. They and their co-members are ready for the Big Sweethearts' Ball at Duquesne Garden Wednesday evening, February 12th, when Jimmie Lunceford and his celebrated orchestra will play the music.  it wil [sic] be one of the most spectacular events of the season.  Left to right: Rosalyn [Roslyn] Lindsay, Romaine Denning, Eloise Robinson, Helen Douglass, Ruth Buchanan, Alyce Lindsay, Barbara Jones."
TitMainTitle: Debs About Town members, from left: Roslyn Lindsay, Romaine Denning, Eloise Robinson, Helen Douglass, Ruth Buchanan, Alyce or Alice Lindsay, and Barbara Jones, posed on step outside University of Pittsburgh's Falk School
